    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors were scoped out as not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 5. The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. It is noted that the validation dataset does not cover dimensional tolerance edge cases at the manufacturing boundary; this limitation is consistent with standard practice for MRL 2 assessments and is considered acceptable. The relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1) is met across all five evaluated operating points. The assessment team accepts the model for the stated COU.",
